That's all, folks!

What a delightful contest we've run here! All told, we came away with some 119 entries from 34 different teams and a sum total of 84 contributing authors, of which **103 articles** from **24 teams** ended up qualifying for victory! For our first team contest in over a year, this was a wonderful showing of creativity, co-operation, and celebrating for our common literary heritage. The Public Domain is wonderful exactly because anyone can take from it and endlessly reimagine and reinterpret -- and having read every qualifying entry, I can assure you that you guys produced some really fantastic reimaginings and reinterpretations of public domain characters from Odysseus to Tintin. This has been a wonderful contest to run, and thank you so much for joining me on it, whether as a participant, reader, or just an observer!

